headline: PayPal (PYPL): Revisiting Valuation After New AI-Focused PYUSD Financing Partnership with USD.AI
summary: PayPal Holdings (PYPL) just caught fresh attention after USD.AI said it will denominate loans to AI companies in PayPal’s PYUSD stablecoin, tying PayPal directly into the financing rails of the AI economy. See our latest analysis for PayPal Holdings. That AI linked PYUSD news lands at an interesting time, with the share price at $58.14 after a 90 day share price return of minus 18.45 percent and a five year total shareholder return of minus 75.97 percent. This suggests longer term momentum...
